ygData.messageBody:
Anyone who received this message from Jimmy Lind, please do not read it, if
you have read it and opened the happy99 program, congratulations you now
have a WORM program, this program is fairly harmless, except that every
email you send will have this happy99.exe program attached to it. You need
to get rid of it immediately.

For further information on this WORM, please go to www.symantec.com, Norton
has a complete description of how to remove this program from your machine.
You do not need an anti-virus program to remove it. Just follow their
directions and it's gone for good.

As for you Jimmy, I hope this was accidental, because sending out these kind
of programs intentially is 1) A felony, 2) For stupid, and morally wrong, 3)
Will get you blacklisted from just about every mailing list there is.

Wenaddar - Network Security Specialist.
